---
import BaseLayout from "../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Installation Guide | Return Architecture"
  description="A practical installation guide for a local environment for continuity, memory, and reflection."
>
  <section class="section">
    <div class="container content-width">
      <div class="eyebrow">Installation Guide</div>
      <h1>A practical path to getting a local setup running.</h1>
      <p>
        This guide is for readers who want a usable local environment without
        needing to be highly technical. The aim is not to remove all complexity,
        but to make the process clearer, more realistic, and easier to follow.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section">
    <div class="container content-width">
      <h2>Who this is for</h2>
      <p>
        This material is intended for capable non-experts and technically
        curious readers who are comfortable installing software, following
        documentation, and making small adjustments as needed.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section">
    <div class="container content-width">
      <h2>What you will need</h2>
      <ul>
        <li>A local machine with enough capacity for the setup you choose.</li>
        <li>A clear sense of whether you want fully local or local-first tools.</li>
        <li>Patience for some configuration and iteration.</li>
        <li>A willingness to keep the setup simple at first.</li>
      </ul>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section">
    <div class="container content-width">
      <h2>Installation approach</h2>
      <p>
        The guide will favor a minimum viable setup first, with optional
        additions later. The goal is to help readers establish a stable
        environment before adding layers of complexity, memory, or extra
        structure.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>
